fields.name: FLASH_PER
fields.desc: program erase resume bit  program erase suspend operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: FLASH_PES
fields.desc: program erase suspend bit  program erase suspend operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: USR
fields.desc: User define command enable.  An operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: FLASH_HPM
fields.desc: Drive Flash into high performance mode.  The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: FLASH_RES
fields.desc: This bit combined with reg_resandres bit releases Flash from the power-down state or high performance mode and obtains the devices ID. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: FLASH_DP
fields.desc: Drive Flash into power down.  An operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: FLASH_CE
fields.desc: Chip erase enable. Chip erase operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: FLASH_BE
fields.desc: Block erase enable. A 64KB block is erased via SPI command D8H.  Block erase operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: FLASH_SE
fields.desc: Sector erase enable. A 4KB sector is erased via SPI command 20H. Sector erase operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: FLASH_PP
fields.desc: Page program enable(1 byte ~256 bytes data to be programmed). Page program operation  will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done .1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: FLASH_WRSR
fields.desc: Write status register enable.   Write status operation  will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: FLASH_RDSR
fields.desc: Read status register-1.  Read status operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: FLASH_RDID
fields.desc: Read JEDEC ID . Read ID command will be sent when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: FLASH_WRDI
fields.desc: Write flash disable. Write disable command will be sent when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: FLASH_WREN
fields.desc: Write flash enable.  Write enable command will be sent when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: FLASH_READ
fields.desc: Read flash enable. Read flash operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: FCS_CRC_EN
fields.desc: For SPI1  initialize crc32 module before writing encrypted data to flash. Active low.

fields.name: TX_CRC_EN
fields.desc: For SPI1  enable crc32 when writing encrypted data to flash. 1: enable  0:disable

fields.name: WAIT_FLASH_IDLE_EN
fields.desc: wait flash idle when program flash or erase flash. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: FASTRD_MODE
fields.desc: This bit enable the bits: spi_fread_qio  spi_fread_dio  spi_fread_qout and spi_fread_dout. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: FREAD_DUAL
fields.desc: In the read operations  read-data phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: RESANDRES
fields.desc: The Device ID is read out to SPI_RD_STATUS register, this bit combine with spi_flash_res bit. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: FREAD_QUAD
fields.desc: In the read operations read-data phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: WP
fields.desc: Write protect signal output when SPI is idle.  1: output high  0: output low.

fields.name: WRSR_2B
fields.desc: two bytes data will be written to status register when it is set. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: FREAD_DIO
fields.desc: In the read operations address phase and read-data phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: FREAD_QIO
fields.desc: In the read operations address phase and read-data phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: RD_BIT_ORDER
fields.desc: In read-data (MISO) phase 1: LSB first 0: MSB first

fields.name: WR_BIT_ORDER
fields.desc: In command address write-data (MOSI) phases 1: LSB firs 0: MSB first

fields.name: CS_HOLD_DELAY_RES
fields.desc: Delay cycles of resume Flash when resume Flash is enable by spi clock.

fields.name: CS_HOLD_DELAY
fields.desc: SPI cs signal is delayed by spi clock cycles

fields.name: STATUS
fields.desc: In the slave mode, it is the status for master to read out.

fields.name: WB_MODE
fields.desc: Mode bits in the flash fast read mode, it is combined with spi_fastrd_mode bit.

fields.name: STATUS_EXT
fields.desc: In the slave mode,it is the status for master to read out.

fields.name: SETUP_TIME
fields.desc: (cycles-1) of ¡°prepare¡± phase by spi clock, this bits combined with spi_cs_setup bit.

fields.name: HOLD_TIME
fields.desc: delay cycles of cs pin by spi clock, this bits combined with spi_cs_hold bit.

fields.name: CK_OUT_LOW_MODE
fields.desc: modify spi clock duty ratio when the value is lager than 8, the bits are combined with spi_clkcnt_N bits and spi_clkcnt_L bits.

fields.name: CK_OUT_HIGH_MODE
fields.desc: modify spi clock duty ratio when the value is lager than 8, the bits are combined with spi_clkcnt_N bits and spi_clkcnt_H bits.

fields.name: MISO_DELAY_MODE
fields.desc: MISO signals are delayed by spi_clk. 0: zero  1: if spi_ck_out_edge or spi_ck_i_edge is set 1  delayed by half cycle    else delayed by one cycle  2: if spi_ck_out_edge or spi_ck_i_edge is set 1  delayed by one cycle  else delayed by half cycle  3: delayed one cycle

fields.name: MISO_DELAY_NUM
fields.desc: MISO signals are delayed by system clock cycles

fields.name: MOSI_DELAY_MODE
fields.desc: MOSI signals are delayed by spi_clk. 0: zero  1: if spi_ck_out_edge or spi_ck_i_edge is set 1  delayed by half cycle    else delayed by one cycle  2: if spi_ck_out_edge or spi_ck_i_edge is set 1  delayed by one cycle  else delayed by half cycle  3: delayed one cycle

fields.name: MOSI_DELAY_NUM
fields.desc: MOSI signals are delayed by system clock cycles

fields.name: CS_DELAY_MODE
fields.desc: spi_cs signal is delayed by spi_clk . 0: zero  1: if spi_ck_out_edge or spi_ck_i_edge is set 1  delayed by half cycle    else delayed by one cycle  2: if spi_ck_out_edge or spi_ck_i_edge is set 1  delayed by one cycle   else delayed by half cycle  3: delayed one cycle

fields.name: CS_DELAY_NUM
fields.desc: spi_cs signal is delayed by system clock cycles

fields.name: CLKCNT_L
fields.desc: In the master mode it must be equal to spi_clkcnt_N. In the slave mode it must be 0.

fields.name: CLKCNT_H
fields.desc: In the master mode it must be floor((spi_clkcnt_N+1)/2-1). In the slave mode it must be 0.

fields.name: CLKCNT_N
fields.desc: In the master mode it is the divider of spi_clk. So spi_clk frequency is system/(spi_clkdiv_pre+1)/(spi_clkcnt_N+1)

fields.name: CLKDIV_PRE
fields.desc: In the master mode it is pre-divider of spi_clk.

fields.name: CLK_EQU_SYSCLK
fields.desc: In the master mode 1: spi_clk is eqaul to system 0: spi_clk is divided from system clock.

fields.name: DOUTDIN
fields.desc: Set the bit to enable full duplex communication. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: CS_HOLD
fields.desc: spi cs keep low when spi is in ¡°done¡± phase. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: CS_SETUP
fields.desc: spi cs is enable when spi is in ¡°prepare¡± phase. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: CK_I_EDGE
fields.desc: In the slave mode  the bit is same as spi_ck_out_edge in master mode. It is combined with  spi_miso_delay_mode bits.

fields.name: CK_OUT_EDGE
fields.desc: the bit combined with spi_mosi_delay_mode bits to set mosi signal delay mode.

fields.name: RD_BYTE_ORDER
fields.desc: In read-data (MISO) phase 1: big-endian 0: little_endian

fields.name: WR_BYTE_ORDER
fields.desc: In command address write-data (MOSI) phases 1: big-endian 0: litte_endian

fields.name: FWRITE_DUAL
fields.desc: In the write operations read-data phase apply 2 signals

fields.name: FWRITE_QUAD

fields.name: FWRITE_DIO
fields.desc: In the write operations address phase and read-data phase apply 2 signals.

fields.name: FWRITE_QIO
fields.desc: In the write operations address phase and read-data phase apply 4 signals.

fields.name: SIO
fields.desc: Set the bit to enable 3-line half duplex communication  mosi and miso signals share the same pin. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: USR_HOLD_POL
fields.desc: It is combined with hold bits to set the polarity of spi hold line  1: spi will be held when spi hold line is high  0: spi will be held when spi hold line is low

fields.name: USR_DOUT_HOLD
fields.desc: spi is hold at data out state  the bit combined with spi_usr_hold_pol bit.

fields.name: USR_DIN_HOLD
fields.desc: spi is hold at data in state  the bit combined with spi_usr_hold_pol bit.

fields.name: USR_DUMMY_HOLD
fields.desc: spi is hold at dummy state  the bit combined with spi_usr_hold_pol bit.

fields.name: USR_ADDR_HOLD
fields.desc: spi is hold at address state  the bit combined with spi_usr_hold_pol bit.

fields.name: USR_CMD_HOLD
fields.desc: spi is hold at command state  the bit combined with spi_usr_hold_pol bit.

fields.name: USR_PREP_HOLD
fields.desc: spi is hold at prepare state  the bit combined with spi_usr_hold_pol bit.

fields.name: USR_MISO_HIGHPART
fields.desc: read-data phase only access to high-part of the buffer spi_w8~spi_w15. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: USR_MOSI_HIGHPART
fields.desc: write-data phase only access to high-part of the buffer spi_w8~spi_w15. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: USR_DUMMY_IDLE
fields.desc: spi clock is disable in dummy phase when the bit is enable.

fields.name: USR_MOSI
fields.desc: This bit enable the write-data phase of an operation.

fields.name: USR_MISO
fields.desc: This bit enable the read-data phase of an operation.

fields.name: USR_DUMMY
fields.desc: This bit enable the dummy phase of an operation.

fields.name: USR_COMMAND

fields.name: RESET_MODE
fields.desc: This bit is used to configure the operating mode of the TWAI Controller. 1: Reset mode; 0: Operating mode.

fields.name: LISTEN_ONLY_MODE
fields.desc: 1: Listen only mode. In this mode the nodes will only receive messages from the bus, without generating the acknowledge signal nor updating the RX error counter.

fields.name: SELF_TEST_MODE
fields.desc: 1: Self test mode. In this mode the TX nodes can perform a successful transmission without receiving the acknowledge signal. This mode is often used to test a single node with the self reception request command.

fields.name: RX_FILTER_MODE
fields.desc: This bit is used to configure the filter mode. 0: Dual filter mode; 1: Single filter mode.

fields.name: TX_REQ
fields.desc: Set the bit to 1 to allow the driving nodes start transmission.

fields.name: ABORT_TX
fields.desc: Set the bit to 1 to cancel a pending transmission request.

fields.name: RELEASE_BUF
fields.desc: Set the bit to 1 to release the RX buffer.

fields.name: CLR_OVERRUN
fields.desc: Set the bit to 1 to clear the data overrun status bit.

fields.name: SELF_RX_REQ
fields.desc: Self reception request command. Set the bit to 1 to allow a message be transmitted and received simultaneously.

fields.name: RX_BUF_ST
fields.desc: 1: The data in the RX buffer is not empty, with at least one received data packet.

fields.name: OVERRUN_ST
fields.desc: 1: The RX FIFO is full and data overrun has occurred.

fields.name: TX_BUF_ST
fields.desc: 1: The TX buffer is empty, the CPU may write a message into it.

fields.name: TX_COMPLETE
fields.desc: 1: The TWAI controller has successfully received a packet from the bus.

fields.name: RX_ST
fields.desc: 1: The TWAI Controller is receiving a message from the bus.

fields.name: TX_ST
fields.desc: 1: The TWAI Controller is transmitting a message to the bus.

fields.name: ERR_ST
fields.desc: 1: At least one of the RX/TX error counter has reached or exceeded the value set in register TWAI_ERR_WARNING_LIMIT_REG.

fields.name: BUS_OFF_ST
fields.desc: 1: In bus-off status, the TWAI Controller is no longer involved in bus activities.

fields.name: MISS_ST
fields.desc: This bit reflects whether the data packet in the RX FIFO is complete. 1: The current packet is missing; 0: The current packet is complete

fields.name: RX_INT_ST
fields.desc: Receive interrupt. If this bit is set to 1, it indicates there are messages to be handled in the RX FIFO.

fields.name: TX_INT_ST
fields.desc: Transmit interrupt. If this bit is set to 1, it indicates the message transmitting mis- sion is finished and a new transmission is able to execute.

fields.name: ERR_WARN_INT_ST
fields.desc: Error warning interrupt. If this bit is set to 1, it indicates the error status signal and the bus-off status signal of Status register have changed (e.g., switched from 0 to 1 or from 1 to 0).

fields.name: OVERRUN_INT_ST
fields.desc: Data overrun interrupt. If this bit is set to 1, it indicates a data overrun interrupt is generated in the RX FIFO.

fields.name: ERR_PASSIVE_INT_ST
fields.desc: Error passive interrupt. If this bit is set to 1, it indicates the TWAI Controller is switched between error active status and error passive status due to the change of error counters.

fields.name: ARB_LOST_INT_ST
fields.desc: Arbitration lost interrupt. If this bit is set to 1, it indicates an arbitration lost interrupt is generated.

fields.name: BUS_ERR_INT_ST
fields.desc: Error interrupt. If this bit is set to 1, it indicates an error is detected on the bus.

fields.name: RX_INT_ENA
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1 to enable receive interrupt.

fields.name: TX_INT_ENA
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1 to enable transmit interrupt.

fields.name: ERR_WARN_INT_ENA
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1 to enable error warning interrupt.

fields.name: OVERRUN_INT_ENA
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1 to enable data overrun interrupt.

fields.name: ERR_PASSIVE_INT_ENA
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1 to enable error passive interrupt.

fields.name: ARB_LOST_INT_ENA
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1 to enable arbitration lost interrupt.

fields.name: BUS_ERR_INT_ENA
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1 to enable error interrupt.

fields.name: BAUD_PRESC
fields.desc: Baud Rate Prescaler, determines the frequency dividing ratio.

fields.name: SYNC_JUMP_WIDTH
fields.desc: Synchronization Jump Width (SJW), 1 \verb+~+ 14 Tq wide.

fields.name: TIME_SEG1
fields.desc: The width of PBS1.

fields.name: TIME_SEG2
fields.desc: The width of PBS2.

fields.name: TIME_SAMP
fields.desc: The number of sample points. 0: the bus is sampled once; 1: the bus is sampled three times

fields.name: ARB_LOST_CAP
fields.desc: This register contains information about the bit position of lost arbitration.

fields.name: ECC_SEGMENT
fields.desc: This register contains information about the location of errors, see Table 181 for details.

fields.name: ECC_DIRECTION
fields.desc: This register contains information about transmission direction of the node when error occurs. 1: Error occurs when receiving a message; 0: Error occurs when transmitting a message

fields.name: ECC_TYPE
fields.desc: This register contains information about error types: 00: bit error; 01: form error; 10: stuff error; 11: other type of error

fields.name: ERR_WARNING_LIMIT
fields.desc: Error warning threshold. In the case when any of a error counter value exceeds the threshold, or all the error counter values are below the threshold, an error warning interrupt will be triggered (given the enable signal is valid).

fields.name: RX_ERR_CNT
fields.desc: The RX error counter register, reflects value changes under reception status.

fields.name: TX_ERR_CNT
fields.desc: The TX error counter register, reflects value changes under transmission status.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_0
fields.desc: In reset mode, it is acceptance code register 0 with R/W Permission. In operation mode, it stores the 0th byte information of the data to be transmitted under operating mode.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_1
fields.desc: In reset mode, it is acceptance code register 1 with R/W Permission. In operation mode, it stores the 1st byte information of the data to be transmitted under operating mode.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_2
fields.desc: In reset mode, it is acceptance code register 2 with R/W Permission. In operation mode, it stores the 2nd byte information of the data to be transmitted under operating mode.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_3
fields.desc: In reset mode, it is acceptance code register 3 with R/W Permission. In operation mode, it stores the 3rd byte information of the data to be transmitted under operating mode.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_4
fields.desc: In reset mode, it is acceptance mask register 0 with R/W Permission. In operation mode, it stores the 4th byte information of the data to be transmitted under operating mode.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_5
fields.desc: In reset mode, it is acceptance mask register 1 with R/W Permission. In operation mode, it stores the 5th byte information of the data to be transmitted under operating mode.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_6
fields.desc: In reset mode, it is acceptance mask register 2 with R/W Permission. In operation mode, it stores the 6th byte information of the data to be transmitted under operating mode.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_7
fields.desc: In reset mode, it is acceptance mask register 3 with R/W Permission. In operation mode, it stores the 7th byte information of the data to be transmitted under operating mode.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_8
fields.desc: Stored the 8th byte information of the data to be transmitted under operating mode.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_9
fields.desc: Stored the 9th byte information of the data to be transmitted under operating mode.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_10
fields.desc: Stored the 10th byte information of the data to be transmitted under operating mode.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_11
fields.desc: Stored the 11th byte information of the data to be transmitted under operating mode.

fields.name: TX_BYTE_12
fields.desc: Stored the 12th byte information of the data to be transmitted under operating mode.

fields.name: RX_MESSAGE_COUNTER
fields.desc: This register reflects the number of messages available within the RX FIFO.

fields.name: CD
fields.desc: These bits are used to configure frequency dividing coefficients of the external CLKOUT pin.

fields.name: CLOCK_OFF
fields.desc: This bit can be configured under reset mode. 1: Disable the external CLKOUT pin; 0: Enable the external CLKOUT pin

fields.name: RXFIFO_RD_BYTE
fields.desc: This register stores one byte data  read by rx fifo.

fields.name: RXFIFO_FULL_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver receives more data than (rx_flow_thrhd_h3 rx_flow_thrhd).

fields.name: TXFIFO_EMPTY_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when the amount of data in transmitter's fifo is less than ((tx_mem_cnttxfifo_cnt) .

fields.name: PARITY_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects the parity error of data.

fields.name: FRM_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects data's frame error .

fields.name: RXFIFO_OVF_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver receives more data than the fifo can store.

fields.name: DSR_CHG_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects the edge change of dsrn signal.

fields.name: CTS_CHG_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects the edge change of ctsn signal.

fields.name: BRK_DET_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects the 0 after the stop bit.

fields.name: RXFIFO_TOUT_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver takes more time than rx_tout_thrhd to receive a byte.

fields.name: SW_XON_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver receives xoff char with uart_sw_flow_con_en is set to 1.

fields.name: SW_XOFF_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver receives xon char with uart_sw_flow_con_en is set to 1.

fields.name: GLITCH_DET_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects the start bit.

fields.name: TX_BRK_DONE_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when transmitter completes  sendding  0 after all the datas in transmitter's fifo are send.

fields.name: TX_BRK_IDLE_DONE_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when transmitter has kept the shortest duration after the  last data has been send.

fields.name: TX_DONE_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when transmitter has send all the data in fifo.

fields.name: RS485_PARITY_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when rs485 detects the parity error.

fields.name: RS485_FRM_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when rs485 detects the data frame error.

fields.name: RS485_CLASH_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when rs485 detects the clash between transmitter and receiver.

fields.name: AT_CMD_CHAR_DET_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects the configured at_cmd chars.

fields.name: RXFIFO_FULL_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the status bit for rxfifo_full_int_raw when rxfifo_full_int_ena is set to 1.

fields.name: TX_BRK_IDLE_DONE_INT_ST

fields.name: TX_DONE_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the status bit for tx_done_int_raw when tx_done_int_ena is set to 1.

fields.name: RS485_PARITY_ERR_INT_ST
fields.desc: This is the status bit for rs485_parity_err_int_raw when rs485_parity_int_ena is set to 1.

fields.desc: This is the status bit for at_cmd_det_int_raw when at_cmd_char_det_int_ena is set to 1.

fields.name: CLKDIV
fields.desc: The register value is  the  integer part of the frequency divider's factor.

fields.name: FRAG
fields.desc: The register  value is the decimal part of the frequency divider's factor.

fields.name: EN
fields.desc: This is the enable bit for detecting baudrate.

fields.name: GLITCH_FILT
fields.desc: when input pulse width is lower then this value igore this pulse.this register is used in autobaud detect process.

fields.name: RXFIFO_CNT
fields.desc: (rx_mem_cnt rxfifo_cnt) stores the byte num of valid datas in receiver's fifo. rx_mem_cnt register stores the 3 most significant bits  rxfifo_cnt stores the 8 least significant bits.

fields.name: ST_URX_OUT
fields.desc: This register stores the value of receiver's finite state machine. 0:RX_IDLE  1:RX_STRT  2:RX_DAT0  3:RX_DAT1  4:RX_DAT2  5:RX_DAT3  6:RX_DAT4  7:RX_DAT5  8:RX_DAT6  9:RX_DAT7   10:RX_PRTY   11:RX_STP1  12:RX_STP2 13:RX_DL1

fields.name: DSRN
fields.desc: This register stores the level value of the internal uart dsr signal.

fields.name: CTSN
fields.desc: This register stores the level value of the internal uart cts signal.

fields.name: RXD
fields.desc: This register stores the level value of the internal uart rxd signal.

fields.name: TXFIFO_CNT
fields.desc: (tx_mem_cnt txfifo_cnt) stores the byte num of valid datas in transmitter's fifo.tx_mem_cnt stores the 3 most significant bits  txfifo_cnt stores the 8 least significant bits.

fields.name: ST_UTX_OUT
fields.desc: This register stores the value of transmitter's finite state machine. 0:TX_IDLE  1:TX_STRT  2:TX_DAT0  3:TX_DAT1  4:TX_DAT2   5:TX_DAT3 6:TX_DAT4  7:TX_DAT5  8:TX_DAT6 9:TX_DAT7  10:TX_PRTY   11:TX_STP1  12:TX_STP2  13:TX_DL0   14:TX_DL1

fields.name: DTRN
fields.desc: The register represent the level value of the internal uart dsr signal.

fields.name: RTSN
fields.desc: This register represent the level value of the internal uart cts signal.

fields.name: TXD
fields.desc: This register represent the  level value of the internal uart rxd signal.

fields.name: PARITY
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the parity check mode.  0:even 1:odd

fields.name: PARITY_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable uart parity check.

fields.name: BIT_NUM
fields.desc: This registe is used to set the length of data:  0:5bits 1:6bits 2:7bits 3:8bits

fields.name: STOP_BIT_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to set the length of  stop bit. 1:1bit  2:1.5bits  3:2bits

fields.name: SW_RTS
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the software rts signal which is used in software flow control.

fields.name: SW_DTR
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the software dtr signal which is used in software flow control..

fields.name: TXD_BRK
fields.desc: Set this bit to enbale transmitter to  send 0 when the process of sending data is done.

fields.name: IRDA_DPLX
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable irda loopback mode.

fields.name: IRDA_TX_EN
fields.desc: This is the start enable bit for irda transmitter.

fields.name: IRDA_WCTL
fields.desc: 1.the irda transmitter's 11th bit is the same to the 10th bit. 0.set irda transmitter's 11th bit to 0.

fields.name: IRDA_TX_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to inverse the level value of  irda transmitter's level.

fields.name: IRDA_RX_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to inverse the level value of irda receiver's level.

fields.name: LOOPBACK
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable uart loopback test mode.

fields.name: TX_FLOW_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable transmitter's flow control function.

fields.name: IRDA_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable irda protocol.

fields.name: RXFIFO_RST
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset uart receiver's fifo.

fields.name: TXFIFO_RST
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset uart transmitter's fifo.

fields.name: RXD_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart rxd signal.

fields.name: CTS_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart cts signal.

fields.name: DSR_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart dsr signal.

fields.name: TXD_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart txd signal.

fields.name: RTS_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart rts signal.

fields.name: DTR_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart dtr signal.

fields.name: CLK_EN
fields.desc: 1.force clock on for registers.support clock only when write registers

fields.name: ERR_WR_MASK
fields.desc: 1.receiver stops storing data int fifo when data is wrong. 0.receiver stores the data even if the  received data is wrong.

fields.name: TICK_REF_ALWAYS_ON
fields.desc: This register is used to select the clock.1.apb clock 0:ref_tick

fields.name: RXFIFO_FULL_THRHD
fields.desc: When receiver receives more data than its threshold value.receiver will produce rxfifo_full_int_raw interrupt.the threshold value is (rx_flow_thrhd_h3 rxfifo_full_thrhd).

fields.name: TXFIFO_EMPTY_THRHD
fields.desc: when the data amount in transmitter fifo is less than its threshold value. it will produce txfifo_empty_int_raw interrupt. the threshold value is (tx_mem_empty_thrhd txfifo_empty_thrhd)

fields.name: RX_FLOW_THRHD
fields.desc: when receiver receives more data than its threshold value. receiver produce signal to tell the transmitter stop transferring data. the threshold value is (rx_flow_thrhd_h3 rx_flow_thrhd).

fields.name: RX_FLOW_EN
fields.desc: This is the flow enable bit for uart receiver. 1:choose software flow control with configuring sw_rts signal

fields.name: RX_TOUT_THRHD
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the timeout value for uart receiver receiving a byte.

fields.name: RX_TOUT_EN
fields.desc: This is the enble bit for uart receiver's timeout function.

fields.name: MIN_CNT
fields.desc: This register stores the value of the minimum duration time for the low level pulse. it is used in baudrate-detect process.

fields.name: MIN_CNT
fields.desc: This register stores  the value of the maxinum duration time for the high level pulse. it is used in baudrate-detect process.

fields.name: RXD_EDGE_CNT
fields.desc: This register stores the count of rxd edge change. it is used in baudrate-detect process.

fields.name: SW_FLOW_CON_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable software  flow control. it is used with register sw_xon or sw_xoff .

fields.name: XONOFF_DEL
fields.desc: Set this bit to remove flow control char from the received data.

fields.name: FORCE_XON
fields.desc: Set this bit to clear ctsn to stop the  transmitter from sending data.

fields.name: FORCE_XOFF
fields.desc: Set this bit to set ctsn to enable the transmitter to go on sending data.

fields.name: SEND_XON
fields.desc: Set this bit to send xon char. it is cleared by hardware automatically.

fields.name: SEND_XOFF
fields.desc: Set this bit to send xoff char. it is cleared by hardware automatically.

fields.name: ACTIVE_THRESHOLD
fields.desc: When the input rxd edge changes more than this register value. the uart is active from light sleeping mode.

fields.name: XON_THRESHOLD
fields.desc: when the data amount in receiver's fifo is more than this register value. it will send a xoff char with uart_sw_flow_con_en set to 1.

fields.name: XOFF_THRESHOLD
fields.desc: When the data amount in receiver's fifo is less than this register value. it will send a xon char with uart_sw_flow_con_en set to 1.

fields.name: XON_CHAR
fields.desc: This register stores the xon flow control char.

fields.name: XOFF_CHAR
fields.desc: This register stores the xoff flow control char.

fields.name: RX_IDLE_THRHD
fields.desc: when receiver takes more time than this register value to receive a byte data. it will produce frame end signal for uhci to stop receiving data.

fields.name: TX_IDLE_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the duration time between transfers.

fields.name: TX_BRK_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the num of 0 send after the process of sending data is done. it is active when txd_brk is set to 1.

fields.name: RS485_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to choose rs485 mode.

fields.name: DL0_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to delay the stop bit by 1 bit.

fields.name: DL1_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to delay the stop bit by 1 bit.

fields.name: RS485TX_RX_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable loopback transmitter's output data signal to receiver's input data signal.

fields.name: RS485RXBY_TX_EN
fields.desc: 1: enable rs485's transmitter to send data when rs485's receiver is busy. 0:rs485's transmitter should not send data when its receiver is busy.

fields.name: RS485_RX_DLY_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to delay the receiver's internal data signal.

fields.name: RS485_TX_DLY_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to delay the transmitter's internal data signal.

fields.name: PRE_IDLE_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the idle duration time before the first at_cmd is received by receiver. when the the duration is less than this register value it will not take the next data received as at_cmd char.

fields.name: POST_IDLE_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the duration time between the last at_cmd and the next data. when the duration is less than this register value  it will not take the previous data as at_cmd char.

fields.name: RX_GAP_TOUT
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the duration time between the at_cmd chars. when the duration time is less than this register value it will not take the datas as continous at_cmd chars.

fields.name: AT_CMD_CHAR
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the content of at_cmd char.

fields.name: CHAR_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the num of continous at_cmd chars received by receiver.

fields.name: MEM_PD
fields.desc: Set this bit to power down mem.when reg_mem_pd registers in the 3 uarts are all set to 1  mem will enter low power mode.

fields.name: RX_SIZE
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the amount of mem allocated to receiver's fifo. the default byte num is 128.

fields.name: TX_SIZE
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the amount of mem allocated to transmitter's fifo.the default byte num is 128.

fields.desc: Set this bit to enable loop test for out links.

fields.name: OUT_NO_RESTART_CLR

fields.desc: Set this bit to produce eof after DMA pops all data  clear this bit to produce eof after DMA pushes all data

fields.desc: Set this bit to use UART to transmit or receive data.

fields.name: UART1_CE
fields.desc: Set this bit to use UART1 to transmit or receive data.

fields.name: UART2_CE
fields.desc: Set this bit to use UART2 to transmit or receive data.

fields.name: OUTDSCR_BURST_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable DMA in links to use burst mode.

fields.name: INDSCR_BURST_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable DMA out links to use burst mode.

fields.name: OUT_DATA_BURST_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable DMA burst MODE

fields.name: SEPER_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to use special char to separate the data frame.

fields.name: HEAD_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable to use head packet  before the data frame.

fields.name: CRC_REC_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable receiver''s ability of crc calculation  when crc_en bit in head packet is 1 then there will be crc bytes after data_frame

fields.name: UART_IDLE_EOF_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable to use idle time  when the idle time after data frame is satisfied  this means the end of a data frame.

fields.name: LEN_EOF_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable to use packet_len in packet head  when the received data is equal to packet_len  this means the end of a data frame.

fields.name: ENCODE_CRC_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable crc calculation for data frame when bit6 in the head packet is 1.

fields.name: CLK_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable clock-gating for read or write registers.

fields.name: UART_RX_BRK_EOF_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable to use brk char as the end of a data frame.

fields.name: RX_HUNG_INT_RAW
fields.desc: when DMA takes a lot of time to receive a data   it will produce uhci_rx_hung_int interrupt.

fields.desc: when a data packet has been received  it will produce uhci_in_suc_eof_int interrupt.

fields.name: IN_ERR_EOF_INT_RAW
fields.desc: when there are some errors about eof in in link descriptor  it will produce uhci_in_err_eof_int interrupt.

fields.name: OUT_DONE_INT_RAW
fields.desc: when a out link descriptor is completed  it will produce uhci_out_done_int interrupt.

fields.desc: when the current descriptor's eof bit is 1  it will produce uhci_out_eof_int interrupt.

fields.name: IN_DSCR_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: when there are some errors about the out link descriptor  it will produce uhci_in_dscr_err_int interrupt.

fields.name: OUT_DSCR_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: when there are some errors about the in link descriptor  it will produce uhci_out_dscr_err_int interrupt.

fields.name: IN_DSCR_EMPTY_INT_RAW
fields.desc: when there are not enough in links for DMA it will produce uhci_in_dscr_err_int interrupt.

fields.name: OUTLINK_EOF_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: when there are some errors about eof in outlink descriptor  it will produce uhci_outlink_eof_err_int interrupt.

fields.name: OUT_TOTAL_EOF_INT_RAW
fields.desc: When all data have been send  it will produce uhci_out_total_eof_int interrupt.

fields.desc: When use always_send registers to send a series of short packets it will produce this interrupt when dma has send the short packet.
